@node LEVELWARPS "DANGER! Warping with mixed level..."

  Let's say there is a warp from level 4 to level 15. Let me call
  level 4 the source level and level 15 the destination level. Okay.

  First problem: You don't know when the source level appears. If the
    source level (here number 4) has been mixed to a position after
    its original position (let's say 22) then you will warp backwards!

    This could also used in the other direction, which is very good:
    the original level 34 with a warp to level 46 has been mixed into
    position 3. You will actually warp from level 3 to the level which
    has been mixed into position 46.

  Second problem: You don't know the destination level and also the
    following levels. These levels can be harder than the levels after
    the source level. The next level after the source level may also
    have a warp to 'higher' levels.

    Let's add a warp from level 9 to level 28. While playing level 4
    appears in first position, level 9 in second position. Let's say
    in positions 15 to 18 you may have these levels: 42,37,22,47. And
    in positions 28 to 30 these levels appear: 11,31,8.
    Would you use the warp from level 4 ? NO, of course not! The levels
    from position 15 to 18 are much harder and may be skipped with the
    warp from level 9 which would come next.

  Summary: Warpes are unpredictable when you mix the levels. In fact
    it's possible to create a circle. But you can collect much points!

@endnode
