@node INSTALL "Install to HD or Floppy"


  Hard disc:
  ~~~~~~~~~~
    Only copy all files into your desired drawer.


  Floppy disc:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    First copy all files in the root directory of a bootable disc and
    create one suitable "s/startup-sequence":

     - boot game only:
         DiamChallV1_31

     - boot editor only:
         DC_EditorV1_3

     - boot selection:
         ECHO "Welcome to Diamond Challenge V1.31"
         LAB Loop
         ASK "Start editor (y/n) ?"
         IF WARN
           DC_EditorV1_3
         ELSE
           DiamChallV1_31
         ENDIF
         SKIP Loop BACK

       Don't forget to add all required commands from your workbench
       disk: ECHO, ASK, IF, ELSE, ENDIF and SKIP.

     - boot to workbench:
         LOADWB
         ENDCLI

       Don't forget to add all required commands from your workbench
       disk: LOADWB and ENDLCI. Refer to your Workbench manual ;-)
       for additional files. This depends on your workbench version.

    That's it. Contanct @{"me" link INFOS}, if you have problems.


  WinUAE and other Amiga emulators:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Hmmm... I just about to buy a PC, so I couldn't test this by mself.
    In general follow the 'floppy disc' installation above. If you need
    help, contact me and I will create a booting disc for you. Always
    copy my default level files "DEFAULT.LEV" and "DEFAULT.SCR" on the
